com.kuka.processdata

Interface IProcessData


  • public interface IProcessData
    Interface describing a process data element.

    The user can get specific process data elements by using the <getProcessData and tryGetProcessData methods of the IProcessDataManager interface.

    By using the IProcessData interface, the user can get and change information of a process data element. The user can also add and remove listeners to be notified if the process data element is changed.

    Data types held as value of an IProcessData object must be immutable and serializable.

    This type can be instantiated in applications and background tasks via dependency injection, using @Inject, @Named etc.
    The @Named annotation can be used to differentiate between different objects of the same type like process data.
    More detailed information including code examples can be found in the documentation of the base class of the application or background task.

    • Method Detail

      • addProcessDataListener

        void addProcessDataListener(IProcessDataListener listener)
        Registers a listener for events regarding process data element changes.

        The user can register an IProcessDataListener and implement custom behavior in the onProcessDataValueChanged(IProcessData) method. Listeners are called asynchronously and sequentially when the process data is changed, the order of the called listeners is not guaranteed.

        Parameters:
        listener - to be registered

      • removeProcessDataListener

        void removeProcessDataListener(IProcessDataListener listener)
        Unregisters a process data listener.
        Parameters:
        listener - to be unregistered

      • isVisibleOn

        boolean isVisibleOn(String channelId)
        Indicates whether this process data element is visible on the given channel.

        In case the given channel is not defined on the process data element, false will be returned.

        Parameters:
        channelId - The unique channel id.
        Returns:
        true, in case the process data element is visible

      • isEditableOn

        boolean isEditableOn(String channelId)
        Indicates whether this process data element is writable on the given channel.

        In case the given channel is not defined on the process data element, false will be returned.

        Parameters:
        channelId - The unique channel id.
        Returns:
        true, in case the process data element is writable
